Package com.stuypulse.stuylib.input

Class Gamepad

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.stuypulse.stuylib.input.Gamepad
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NetKeyGamepad, WPIGamepad
    public class Gamepad
extends java.lang.Object
    An class for using gamepads with different interfaces. You can implement this class in another file, and then use it with a standard interface. Any unimplemented buttons will never be triggered, so if a certain controller is missing one, dont worry about it. The button type that is used in OI.java is automatically generated by this class, as long as you implement the getRaw...() function, the get...() function will work. This class does not come with a constructor because by itself, the class does not do anything. You need to extend this class inorder to use it.
